contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:01.500 --> 01:03.300
- Wait, wait, wait, wait, wait...

01:16.820 --> 01:18.180
Get dressed.

01:39.460 --> 01:41.220
[DOOR CLOSES]

01:41.220 --> 01:45.380
News just coming in. We have several
unconfirmed reports

01:45.380 --> 01:47.300
of multiple casualties at a shrine

01:47.300 --> 01:51.300
set up in memory of helpline
volunteer Jamie Unwin. A young

01:51.300 --> 01:55.380
woman who was brutally killed on the
same spot just two days ago.

01:55.380 --> 01:58.660
Police say they are unable at this
time to confirm or deny

01:58.660 --> 02:01.660
any link to yesterday's so-called
Good Samaritan murder

02:01.660 --> 02:03.580
on a local bus.

02:03.580 --> 02:06.420
Police are urging members of the
public to remain vigilant,

02:06.420 --> 02:09.820
and to avoid approaching anyone
claiming to need help

02:09.820 --> 02:12.500
or anyone seemingly in distress.

02:12.500 --> 02:15.780
What are your thoughts? Do you feel
safe on our streets?

02:15.780 --> 02:20.540
Phone in now on 08081570999.

02:22.020 --> 02:23.820
- Eyewitnesses didn't see much.

02:23.820 --> 02:26.300
One of them saw a man kneel to put
that head down.

02:26.300 --> 02:28.380
She's with the sketch artist now.

02:28.380 --> 02:31.740
That's Jason Walker, him and his
news team, totally wiped out.

02:31.740 --> 02:33.460
Nobody tried to help - too scared.

02:33.460 --> 02:36.060
- So first he brings Jamie Unwin to
this spot.

02:36.060 --> 02:39.420
We assumed he was looking for
maximum visibility,

02:39.420 --> 02:41.020
maximum shock value.

02:41.020 --> 02:43.500
- Well, he's succeeded.

02:43.500 --> 02:45.140
- But maybe he knew he'd be coming
back.

02:45.140 --> 02:47.380
- Knew he'd be back?
- Yeah.

02:47.380 --> 02:50.460
Yeah, young woman like Jamie Unwin
dies in circumstances like this,

02:50.460 --> 02:53.900
it's a fair bet a shrine's going to
spring up, bring the media with it.

02:55.740 --> 02:58.220
I need the last footage that this
took.

02:58.220 --> 02:59.380
- He took it.

02:59.380 --> 03:00.500
- What?!

03:00.500 --> 03:02.620
- These things hold standard SDXC
memory cards.

03:02.620 --> 03:04.140
The killer took them both.

03:04.140 --> 03:05.740
- Where's DCI Hicks?

03:05.740 --> 03:07.940
- He says he'll see us at Lethe
Road.

03:43.140 --> 03:45.940
- We started going out when I was
14.

03:45.940 --> 03:48.300
Everyone loved him.

03:48.300 --> 03:51.540
I mean, he was handsome and good at
sport, all that.

03:53.140 --> 03:58.100
But he was kind, too. I couldn't
believe he was my boyfriend.

03:59.420 --> 04:02.140
Then I couldn't believe he was my
husband.

04:03.780 --> 04:07.940
I'd hear all these other women
moaning about their husbands

04:07.940 --> 04:12.100
and I-I'd feel guilty because Alex
wasn't like that at all.

04:14.780 --> 04:17.260
I mean, at all.

04:18.700 --> 04:21.019
I'm sorry, I just...

04:22.620 --> 04:24.940
I just can't believe he's gone.

04:26.380 --> 04:28.540
I just can't believe it.

04:29.820 --> 04:32.180
- Oh, Jesus, Elaine.

04:45.740 --> 04:48.820
- ♪ Blue moon

04:48.820 --> 04:51.820
♪ You saw me standing alone. ♪

04:54.140 --> 04:55.940
[HE CHUCKLES]

05:00.900 --> 05:03.060
[DOOR SLAMS, WHISTLING]

06:35.580 --> 06:37.420
- Do you know why I'm here?

06:37.420 --> 06:39.060
- No.

06:40.820 --> 06:43.500
- Do you know who I am?

06:43.500 --> 06:45.340
- No.

06:46.500 --> 06:48.340
- Well, I know who you are.

06:52.380 --> 06:55.020
It must eat you alive.

06:55.020 --> 06:57.380
Being silenced.

06:57.380 --> 07:00.580
Because they can't bear the truth of
it.

07:14.980 --> 07:17.660
- Please... don't do this... please.

07:37.180 --> 07:39.700
Oh, Jesus!

07:39.700 --> 07:41.060
Oh, God!

07:43.540 --> 07:46.260
- I'm giving you your life back.

07:48.860 --> 07:52.540
In exchange, I want you to give me a
voice.

07:52.540 --> 07:55.460
I'll be watching, Will.

08:34.020 --> 08:37.900
- ...now just a few hours ago, an
estimated 300 people

08:37.900 --> 08:40.980
were stood on this spot, some
singing, some praying...

08:40.980 --> 08:43.700
- Keep filming or he dies.

08:43.700 --> 08:45.940
The Hard Sun is coming.

08:45.940 --> 08:48.260
And I am its messenger.

08:52.140 --> 08:54.180
[DOOR CLOSES]

09:18.540 --> 09:23.860
- Listen, Will, I know you see this
as being a way back into the game,

09:23.860 --> 09:26.100
but it's not going to happen.

09:27.140 --> 09:30.820
- Except, you know everyone's going
to want this, Alan.

09:32.460 --> 09:36.660
And here you are at the sorry end of
a career in a dying industry,

09:36.660 --> 09:39.780
editing a third-rate click-bait
engine that you hate

09:39.780 --> 09:41.460
and don't even understand.

09:42.740 --> 09:45.580
When was the last time you had an
actual scoop, Alan?

09:47.180 --> 09:51.500
And more to the point, when's it
ever going to happen again?

09:57.060 --> 10:00.900
- All right, you lovely people, have
we caught him yet?

10:00.900 --> 10:02.540
If not, why not?

10:02.540 --> 10:05.380
- Er, forensics got footprints at
the allotments.

10:05.380 --> 10:06.860
Size nine and a half,

10:06.860 --> 10:09.780
tread pattern consistent with German
paratrooper boots.

10:09.780 --> 10:11.940
- These are being circulated as we
speak.

10:13.260 --> 10:16.940
Narrows it down to about eleventy
million people.

10:16.940 --> 10:18.900
- Where'd he get this?

10:18.900 --> 10:22.420
- Well, it turns out there are 52
Catholic churches in London,

10:22.420 --> 10:24.740
hundreds of C of E and other
denominations,

10:24.740 --> 10:27.540
and right now, it's about five
o'clock in the morning, so...

10:27.540 --> 10:29.620
- Have you checked St Mary's? You
know, Dennis' place?

10:29.620 --> 10:31.380
- Yeah, yeah. First place we looked.

10:38.140 --> 10:39.780
- Come with me, please.

10:43.700 --> 10:45.020
Come on.

10:47.540 --> 10:49.860
This is what your silence is leading
to.

10:51.420 --> 10:52.580
You got it?

10:53.860 --> 10:55.820
I just want to show you this, too.

10:58.380 --> 11:00.060
Who is he, Dennis?

11:00.060 --> 11:01.820
Who is he?!

11:01.820 --> 11:04.220
- Are you going to make me ask
what's going on here?

11:04.220 --> 11:07.220
- Just trying to jog Father Dennis'
memory, boss.

11:07.220 --> 11:08.660
- And can we?

11:10.500 --> 11:12.140
- Apparently not.

11:12.140 --> 11:15.100
- Dandy. Then let's send Father
Dennis home, shall we?

11:15.100 --> 11:17.380
DI Renko, spare me a moment, please?

11:27.140 --> 11:32.660
So, you have concluded that Charlie
Hicks didn't kill Alex Butler,

11:32.660 --> 11:35.220
but the people who put you in place
to run this investigation

11:35.220 --> 11:37.900
don't believe that conclusion to be
supported by the evidence.

11:37.900 --> 11:39.860
- There is no evidence. That's the
point.

11:39.860 --> 11:42.740
- There is a concern you might
become compromised.

11:42.740 --> 11:45.180
As a result of which, the deal you
brokered

11:45.180 --> 11:47.780
has been rendered null and void.

11:47.780 --> 11:51.220
Once he's released from hospital,
Daniel will be transferred to

11:51.220 --> 11:54.100
a maximum-security prison facility
forthwith.

11:54.100 --> 11:56.300
- You can't do that.
- Sit back and watch me.

11:58.580 --> 12:00.060
Unless...

12:00.060 --> 12:01.220
- I give you what you want.

12:01.220 --> 12:03.140
- DCI Hicks is not innocent.

12:03.140 --> 12:05.660
- He's innocent of this.
- So you say.

12:06.860 --> 12:10.980
But if your new pal didn't put that
bullet in Butler's head, who did?

12:10.980 --> 12:13.700
Because if you really want to keep
Daniel from being subjected

12:13.700 --> 12:15.940
to nightly bukkake parties on the
secure wing,

12:15.940 --> 12:18.700
it's not enough to tell me Hicks is
innocent.

12:18.700 --> 12:22.100
Prove it. Bring me whoever did,

12:22.100 --> 12:23.500
soon...

12:25.100 --> 12:26.980
...or it is out of my hands.

12:31.460 --> 12:34.700
- Hey, hey, hey. What was all that
about?

12:34.700 --> 12:36.620
- He knows about Daniel.

12:36.620 --> 12:38.660
He ordered me to take compassionate
leave.

12:38.660 --> 12:42.380
- What, today?
- Yeah. He knows what he can swivel
on.

12:42.380 --> 12:44.260
[BUZZING]

12:44.260 --> 12:45.620
- So, I-I've been chewing this over,

12:45.620 --> 12:49.340
this thing with the news cameras,
the SD cards and what have you.

12:49.340 --> 12:52.220
Now, I'm wondering if it's not about
legitimacy.

12:52.220 --> 12:55.780
I mean, any common or garden Looney
Tunes can put himself on YouTube,

12:55.780 --> 12:59.420
but our boy doesn't think of himself
as common or garden Looney Tunes.

12:59.420 --> 13:02.180
He thinks of himself as news.

13:02.180 --> 13:06.620
So, if he's got something important
to say, what are the chances

13:06.620 --> 13:10.740
he's already tried to say it somehow
and failed?
- Hm.

13:10.740 --> 13:13.100
- Actually, that's not a daft
thought.

13:13.100 --> 13:14.340
- Thank you so much.

13:14.340 --> 13:17.620
- No, I mean, the thing about
lone-actor massacres is,

13:17.620 --> 13:19.580
82% of the time, friends

13:19.580 --> 13:23.060
and family know about the killer's
grievance well in advance, so...

13:23.060 --> 13:24.260
- Whatever his message is,

13:24.260 --> 13:26.300
he's probably tried to get it out
there before.

13:26.300 --> 13:28.500
- Yeah, probably on the internet,
but nobody listened.

13:28.500 --> 13:29.820
[BUZZING]

13:29.820 --> 13:33.460
- So, what if he's decided to go
direct to source? Old-school media.

13:33.460 --> 13:35.380
- TV.
- Or newspaper.

13:40.940 --> 13:42.180
Too late.

13:47.900 --> 13:52.020
- ...it's now just a few hours ago,
an estimated 300 people

13:52.020 --> 13:56.060
were stood on this spot, some
singing, some praying, others...

13:56.060 --> 13:58.140
- Keep filming or he dies.

13:58.140 --> 14:01.460
The Hard Sun is coming.

14:01.460 --> 14:03.300
And I am its messenger.

14:06.940 --> 14:11.140
Hard Sun is coming. Hard Sun is not
God.

14:11.140 --> 14:15.100
God is the Creation and the Light.
God is the Word.

14:15.100 --> 14:18.820
Hard Sun is destruction and darkness
and silence.

14:18.820 --> 14:21.700
You think yourselves good, but
you're monsters.

14:21.700 --> 14:24.340
You consume more than you could ever
need,

14:24.340 --> 14:28.060
while all over the world children
die in misery.

14:28.060 --> 14:31.180
Your gluttony is a holocaust of dead
infants.

14:31.180 --> 14:34.340
Your charity is nourished by death
and despair.

14:34.340 --> 14:36.620
Your charity is your hypocrisy

14:36.620 --> 14:39.060
and your hypocrisy is your death
sentence.

14:39.060 --> 14:40.460
I'm here to punish you.

14:41.860 --> 14:44.220
This city is an unmarked grave.

14:44.220 --> 14:48.140
But Dennis can stop me. Father
Dennis Chapman can stop me.

14:48.140 --> 14:50.500
- Christ! He's named the priest!

14:50.500 --> 14:54.900
- So breaking news, we have a priest
who knows who the killer is.

14:54.900 --> 14:56.500
This is your time for your thoughts.

14:56.500 --> 14:58.300
We have another caller here,
Richard...

14:58.300 --> 15:02.060
- Yeah, they wonder why the churches
are empty on Sunday morning, they
haven't got a clue!

15:02.060 --> 15:03.340
- Dennis.

15:03.340 --> 15:05.380
- Adam, it's your time, you
called...

15:05.380 --> 15:09.180
- Well, I-I'm a Catholic and I love
my god and my Church, but how can

15:09.180 --> 15:12.580
a priest ever offer absolution to a
murderer who's not repentant?

15:12.580 --> 15:13.900
- That's a very good point, Adam.

15:13.900 --> 15:15.820
- I really think you'd better leave
here.

15:15.820 --> 15:17.060
- We've got time for one more...

16:00.180 --> 16:03.300
- It's the antidepressants. She's
gone all glass-half-full.

16:03.300 --> 16:05.980
- Well, that's not the worst crime
in the world, though, is it?

16:05.980 --> 16:07.660
Being an optimist.

16:07.660 --> 16:10.620
- Yeah. And I mean, it's not like I
don't feel bad about it.

16:10.620 --> 16:14.140
- Hm.
- But she used to be... not
sarcastic,

16:14.140 --> 16:16.660
- but she had, like, this dry wit?
- Hm.

16:16.660 --> 16:19.820
- Now she's all like, "Everything
happens for a reason."

16:19.820 --> 16:21.940
And I'm like, "Actually, no!"

16:21.940 --> 16:23.660
- No, it don't happen for no reason.

16:25.420 --> 16:26.780
Oh.

16:28.580 --> 16:30.340
Hey, what's he doing?

16:32.380 --> 16:34.660
No, is that...

16:34.660 --> 16:36.740
Is that...

16:36.740 --> 16:38.180
Is that petrol?

16:38.180 --> 16:39.860
- Nah!
- I hope not.

16:39.860 --> 16:42.860
- Dude, there's a man in the front
seat, as well. Go, call them.

16:42.860 --> 16:45.020
- Is there?
- Call them, yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.

16:45.020 --> 16:47.260
No! No, no, no, no, no.

16:47.260 --> 16:49.260
Oi, no!

16:50.620 --> 16:52.420
He's got a light! Oi!

16:52.420 --> 16:54.180
No! No, no, no, don't do that!

16:54.180 --> 16:57.860
Don't do that. Don't do that! I said
don't do that!

17:10.980 --> 17:12.140
- Come on out.

17:13.300 --> 17:14.859
Help him out.

18:07.780 --> 18:10.100
- What's going on? Hey, what are
this lot doing here?

18:10.100 --> 18:12.420
- The case has been passed up to
Counter Terrorism.

18:12.420 --> 18:15.540
- What?!
- You'll give them access to all the
evidence collected so far,

18:15.540 --> 18:18.260
and continue working in a support
role.

18:18.260 --> 18:21.100
- Oh, come on. Look, he's just
getting started. You know that!

18:21.100 --> 18:23.580
Look, he's not a name on a Counter
Terrorism database.

18:23.580 --> 18:24.820
He's a murderer.

18:24.820 --> 18:27.620
Look, they'll just keep blundering
after him until they get lucky.

18:27.620 --> 18:30.380
All right, how many people does he
kill between now and then? Huh?

18:30.380 --> 18:31.900
- That may or may not be so,

18:31.900 --> 18:34.740
but as of now, this case belongs to
Counter Terrorism,

18:34.740 --> 18:36.820
who will be dazzled

18:36.820 --> 18:41.500
and charmed by the extent of your
willingness to cooperate.

18:41.500 --> 18:44.940
Let's start by fetching Father
Chapman back for them.

18:46.020 --> 18:49.420
Maybe they'll have more luck
extracting a name than you did.

18:51.020 --> 18:53.220
[RINGING]

18:56.620 --> 18:58.060
Hello.

18:58.060 --> 18:59.260
- Dad?

18:59.260 --> 19:00.700
- Hey, you all right, sweet pea?

19:00.700 --> 19:04.340
- Don't call me that. Is it OK to go
to school?

19:04.340 --> 19:07.460
- Well, that's a new one! What are
you on about?

19:07.460 --> 19:09.620
- I heard it on the news.

19:09.620 --> 19:11.580
What if he comes to my school or
something?

19:11.580 --> 19:12.860
Like happens in America.

19:12.860 --> 19:14.140
- Hey, now you listen here.

19:14.140 --> 19:16.620
Look, he's just some twonk with
1,000 beefy-faced coppers

19:16.620 --> 19:18.100
chasing after him.

19:18.100 --> 19:19.740
- Promise, though?

19:19.740 --> 19:21.740
Cos he's well fearsome.

19:21.740 --> 19:24.540
- "Well fearsome"?! What you on
about?

19:24.540 --> 19:26.820
Look, he's just some wanker in a
mask.

19:26.820 --> 19:28.060
- Dad!

19:28.060 --> 19:29.460
- Well, he is!

19:29.460 --> 19:32.580
Now, you listen to me, young lady -
I will take him one-handed,

19:32.580 --> 19:35.220
with a Jaffa Cake stuffed in my
mouth,

19:35.220 --> 19:38.780
and be home before the chocolate's
melted. How's that?

19:38.780 --> 19:40.580
All right?

19:40.580 --> 19:42.020
All right, love you.

19:42.020 --> 19:43.420
- Love you.

19:45.100 --> 19:46.860
- You want to step away from this?

19:46.860 --> 19:48.020
- Absolutely not.

19:48.020 --> 19:49.100
- OK.

19:49.100 --> 19:50.500
- What's the plan?

19:50.500 --> 19:53.980
- OK, look, we, er, we let the
others show support for Counter
Terrorism,

19:53.980 --> 19:57.460
you know, interview witnesses, turn
the soil.

19:57.460 --> 19:59.380
You take that day as leave?

19:59.380 --> 20:00.820
- Not on your Nelly.

20:00.820 --> 20:03.220
- Right. Well, the boss is still
watching us.

20:03.220 --> 20:05.460
So do what he says. Go and see your
boy.

20:05.460 --> 20:07.380
- What about the priest?

20:07.380 --> 20:09.820
- OK. Look, Dennis is obviously not
going to cooperate -

20:09.820 --> 20:11.620
well, not willingly or deliberately
-

20:11.620 --> 20:14.260
and the killer knows that, so I
think we can use it against him.

20:14.260 --> 20:17.020
You know, tickle him out like a
trout.
- How?

20:17.020 --> 20:18.740
- Unethically.

20:20.060 --> 20:21.540
- Fair play.

20:21.540 --> 20:24.980
- Your mate, the, er, journalist,
the one that went into hiding?

20:24.980 --> 20:26.420
- Will?

20:26.420 --> 20:30.020
- Yeah. We know the killer's
watching him. We can use that.

20:30.020 --> 20:32.020
You think you can track him down?

20:32.020 --> 20:33.100
- Absolutely.

20:33.100 --> 20:34.220
- All right, good.

20:34.220 --> 20:35.380
- Where will you be?

20:38.340 --> 20:39.860
- Probably best you don't know.

21:26.580 --> 21:28.420
- Excuse me, sir, do you have a
second?

21:36.780 --> 21:38.060
- Absolutely.

21:38.060 --> 21:40.860
- Excellent! OK! Did you know that
cancer...

21:40.860 --> 21:42.260
- Why are you doing this?

21:44.100 --> 21:45.820
- Er... for Cancer Action UK.

21:45.820 --> 21:48.340
- OK. But why are YOU doing it?

21:48.340 --> 21:50.740
- I'm sorry, I don't understand.

21:50.740 --> 21:52.420
- Has cancer affected your life?

21:54.260 --> 21:56.940
- Right, with you.

21:56.940 --> 22:04.420
Well, I suppose I know people who it
has affected, so that's why...

22:04.420 --> 22:06.940
- But that's not why you're here,
doing it?

22:06.940 --> 22:09.580
- No. Not-not as such.

22:09.580 --> 22:12.500
But, yeah, well, it's actually a
job, so...

22:12.500 --> 22:15.860
- Which means you're basically a
cancer whore.

22:19.380 --> 22:22.620
- Er, well-well, I wouldn't say
that.

22:24.100 --> 22:27.580
I'm actually... I'm actually a
student. Hotel management.

22:54.140 --> 22:56.980
- Did you see it? Her room?

22:56.980 --> 23:00.460
- Yeah. Yeah, I saw it.

23:00.460 --> 23:03.820
- She's like a feral cat. You don't
want that thing stalking you.

23:05.020 --> 23:06.060
- No.

23:06.060 --> 23:08.580
- I assume the password worked?

23:08.580 --> 23:10.980
So...

23:10.980 --> 23:13.380
...the flash drive?

23:13.380 --> 23:16.780
- Oh, look, you're going to have to
give me a chance here.

23:16.780 --> 23:19.980
You know what she's like. Look,
she's got no-one.

23:19.980 --> 23:24.060
You know, no family. No friends. No
social life. No-one.

23:24.060 --> 23:25.820
No, all she's got is enemies.

23:25.820 --> 23:28.260
- Including her own son.

23:28.260 --> 23:30.620
- Which is why you went after him.

23:30.620 --> 23:32.780
- It was a sound idea, in theory.

23:35.380 --> 23:37.460
- Yeah, what theory was that?

23:37.460 --> 23:43.380
- If all she's got is enemies, which
enemy can she trust the most?

23:52.980 --> 23:54.940
- Look at that...

24:01.740 --> 24:05.020
- He rented the downstairs flat. And
there was just something about him.

24:05.020 --> 24:06.460
I don't know...

24:06.460 --> 24:09.220
- Going on about decadent this and
purifying that...

24:09.220 --> 24:11.820
- Two years ago he went to Macedonia
as an aid worker.

24:11.820 --> 24:13.300
Something happened over there.

24:13.300 --> 24:17.340
He came back and he was...
different.

24:17.340 --> 24:19.980
- I know it sounds mad, but I swear
it was him.

24:19.980 --> 24:24.220
Absolutely swear. I collect money
for cancer research.

24:24.220 --> 24:26.940
He called me a "cancer whore" and
then laughed.

24:42.300 --> 24:43.620
- Did you do this to me?

24:44.820 --> 24:47.060
Allow the press to release my name?

24:47.060 --> 24:49.540
- No. I wouldn't do that.

24:49.540 --> 24:50.900
But listen.

24:52.300 --> 24:54.700
This isn't going to get any easier.

24:54.700 --> 24:57.020
All right, you've been getting a lot
of death threats -

24:57.020 --> 24:58.980
we have to take that very seriously.

24:58.980 --> 25:02.140
You know, a lot of very scared
people are blaming you for this.

25:02.140 --> 25:06.300
- Make him stop! Catch him, for
Christ's sake!

25:06.300 --> 25:08.420
You're the police!

25:08.420 --> 25:12.020
- And you're the only person in
London that knows his name.

25:14.620 --> 25:17.220
Look, things have moved on quite a
bit.

25:17.220 --> 25:19.300
It's being treated as a terrorist
incident.

25:19.300 --> 25:20.820
It's not even my case any more.

25:20.820 --> 25:26.380
Look, I've been sent by Counter
Terrorism to see that you're
protected.

25:26.380 --> 25:28.820
So, if you'd like to accompany me,
please?

25:28.820 --> 25:31.700
- I suppose I don't have any say in
the matter?

25:32.940 --> 25:35.020
- Absolutely none. Sorry.

25:39.340 --> 25:42.220
- ...police presence in London has
been greatly increased.

25:42.220 --> 25:44.780
In related news, officers say
they're concerned

25:44.780 --> 25:48.100
for the safety of Father Dennis
Chapman, who's gone missing from

25:48.100 --> 25:52.020
his parish in Shepherd's Bush after
receiving dozens of death threats.

25:53.420 --> 25:55.060
- It's all kicking off out there.

25:55.060 --> 25:56.540
- Here. Take these.

26:02.380 --> 26:04.700
- Do you think Charlie's all up in
it?

26:04.700 --> 26:06.380
- Who knows?

26:06.380 --> 26:09.300
- Do you think he'll be OK?
- No-one's going to hurt Charlie
Hicks.

26:09.300 --> 26:11.100
- You can't say that, though.

26:11.100 --> 26:14.140
- I can totally say that. In fact, I
think I just heard myself saying
that.

26:14.140 --> 26:15.660
- You didn't say it about Dad.

26:17.580 --> 26:20.340
[RINGING]

26:24.420 --> 26:25.900
- Hello?

26:27.860 --> 26:30.300
I'm sorry. Who is this?

26:42.540 --> 26:43.700
Are you Elaine?

26:43.700 --> 26:44.900
- I am, yeah.

26:44.900 --> 26:47.980
- All right, well, then, what's
happening? What's this about?

26:49.380 --> 26:50.660
- Charlie Hicks.

26:52.460 --> 26:54.380
Listen, I know you two are close,

26:54.380 --> 26:56.140
but can I just be candid here?

26:56.140 --> 26:58.020
- Yeah. Please do. I mean, that'd be
nice.

26:58.020 --> 26:59.820
- And this is in total confidence
now.

26:59.820 --> 27:02.180
- Right. You're actually freaking me
out a bit.

27:05.740 --> 27:08.060
- Do you think he killed your
husband?

27:08.060 --> 27:12.940
- What?! No, of course not! Of
course he didn't!

27:12.940 --> 27:13.980
Jesus!

27:13.980 --> 27:16.380
- For what it's worth, I don't think
so, either.

27:16.380 --> 27:18.340
But some people disagree.

27:18.340 --> 27:19.580
- What people?

27:19.580 --> 27:20.620
- Serious people.

27:22.100 --> 27:23.980
Does he ever talk to you about it?

27:23.980 --> 27:25.620
- No. Why would he?

27:25.620 --> 27:28.220
- He knows they're coming for him,
Mari.

27:28.220 --> 27:30.700
And do you know what he's done to
clear his name? Nothing!

27:30.700 --> 27:34.020
- OK. You're going to need to slow
down for a second cos I'm-I'm-I'm
not following.

27:34.020 --> 27:37.460
- I'm just saying, why would he be
happy to walk around with it hanging
over his head?

27:37.460 --> 27:38.620
- I don't know.

27:38.620 --> 27:40.020
- Nor do I.

27:41.740 --> 27:43.060
Not really.

27:43.060 --> 27:44.860
Basically, I can only think of one
reason.

27:44.860 --> 27:46.020
- And what's that?

27:46.020 --> 27:47.900
- To protect someone he loves.

27:50.300 --> 27:51.900
- Right.

27:51.900 --> 27:54.540
And now are you accusing me of
something?

27:54.540 --> 27:57.820
- I am asking you. Completely off
the record.

27:57.820 --> 28:02.340
If you know anything - anything at
all - about your husband's death,

28:02.340 --> 28:03.460
you've got to tell me.

28:03.460 --> 28:08.220
Please. Because I think Charlie
really needs your help right now.

28:08.220 --> 28:09.780
I really do.

28:13.260 --> 28:15.140
- There's nothing.

28:18.580 --> 28:19.620
- OK.

28:22.020 --> 28:25.180
Can you do me a favour and just
think about it, all right?

28:26.740 --> 28:28.500
Just think about it for me.

28:36.420 --> 28:39.060
- And how do you answer your critics
who say you have to

28:39.060 --> 28:42.100
acknowledge a connection between
these crimes and the Hard Sun hoax

28:42.100 --> 28:43.820
which seems to have ended your
career?

28:43.820 --> 28:46.860
- Well, if my career had been ended,
I wouldn't be sitting here.

28:46.860 --> 28:49.940
- Well, given this man claims to be
motivated at least in part

28:49.940 --> 28:52.500
by that story, do you feel any sense
of responsibility?

28:52.500 --> 28:56.940
- Absolutely not. Look, however
warped his motivation,

28:56.940 --> 29:00.900
however deluded his world view, this
isn't about me.

29:00.900 --> 29:03.580
It's about people's right to know.

30:06.420 --> 30:10.420
- Oh, it's totally demented. We've
got multiple unconfirmed sightings,

30:10.420 --> 30:12.380
hundreds of witnesses,

30:12.380 --> 30:16.220
no usable CCTV footage, dozens of
confessions.

30:16.220 --> 30:18.740
People just keep adding straw onto
the haystack.

30:18.740 --> 30:21.660
The harder we look for him, the more
difficult he is to find.

30:21.660 --> 30:26.780
- Ask George to cross-reference
everyone coming forward against
Dennis' little black address book.

30:26.780 --> 30:28.380
Yeah, just to be sure.

30:28.380 --> 30:29.740
- Got it. Done and done.

30:29.740 --> 30:31.820
- All right.

31:06.660 --> 31:08.340
- What are you doing?

31:08.340 --> 31:10.660
- Oh, I'm sorry. Is there somewhere
you need to be?

31:10.660 --> 31:12.820
- I've got a home.

31:12.820 --> 31:17.420
- Oh, I wouldn't recommend it.
You're the most hated person in
London.

31:19.260 --> 31:21.580
- I'm sure the police can look after
me.

31:23.340 --> 31:25.420
- Well, why should we?

31:25.420 --> 31:30.140
Why should we waste our resources on
someone who refuses to help us?

31:30.140 --> 31:32.420
Or refuses to help himself, for that
matter.

31:34.020 --> 31:36.380
Why'd you become a priest, Dennis?

31:36.380 --> 31:38.540
- Because I wanted to serve God!

31:40.500 --> 31:41.900
- All right.

31:45.860 --> 31:49.980
Well, before that, ever been in love
-

31:49.980 --> 31:52.020
with an actual human being?

31:52.020 --> 31:55.420
- I've loved. And I've been loved.

31:55.420 --> 31:58.820
- And you gave it all up. For God?

31:58.820 --> 32:00.700
- Yeah.

32:00.700 --> 32:03.540
- You never felt like maybe He was
asking for quite a lot?

32:03.540 --> 32:05.340
- Course I did.

32:05.340 --> 32:08.780
- Yeah, I mean, after all that,
after everything you gave up,

32:08.780 --> 32:11.100
you think-you think this is what He
wants for you?

32:11.100 --> 32:13.340
Right here, now? Today?

32:13.340 --> 32:15.980
You've heard of waterboarding, I
expect?

32:17.580 --> 32:20.940
- Stop now, Charlie. Enough.

32:20.940 --> 32:23.340
- I mean, honestly, it's, er,

32:23.340 --> 32:26.940
well, it's one of the worst things
that can happen to someone.

32:26.940 --> 32:30.180
Yeah, even the, er, the Special
Forces...

32:30.180 --> 32:32.860
You know, people that are trained
for it, you know, hard men

32:32.860 --> 32:34.740
and women,

32:34.740 --> 32:37.620
even they can't stand it for more
than a few seconds.

32:37.620 --> 32:40.660
You know, it's only ever used as an
absolute last resort.

32:40.660 --> 32:42.100
It's very effective, though.

32:42.100 --> 32:43.660
- You don't want to do this.

32:43.660 --> 32:45.300
- No, you're right, I don't.

32:45.300 --> 32:46.740
- So don't do it.

32:46.740 --> 32:48.460
- Well, then, don't make me.

32:49.580 --> 32:54.220
- This isn't you, Charlie. You're a
good man.

32:55.860 --> 32:57.580
You have a kind heart.

32:58.620 --> 33:01.700
But you can't hide that kind of
heart.

33:01.700 --> 33:04.020
- I'm a good man, am I?

33:07.940 --> 33:10.260
- You don't need to do this.

33:10.260 --> 33:12.900
- Then tell me what I need to know
and it doesn't have to happen.

33:12.900 --> 33:14.780
- Don't put yourself through this!

33:14.780 --> 33:16.220
- Then let me stop!

33:16.220 --> 33:18.140
- I can't do this!
- You can!

33:18.140 --> 33:20.700
- Who is he?
- For your own sake!

33:20.700 --> 33:22.860
- WHO IS HE?!

33:22.860 --> 33:25.460
- Let me go!

33:25.460 --> 33:27.300
- Go where, Dennis?

33:27.300 --> 33:28.980
Huh? Go where?

33:28.980 --> 33:31.180
I mean, where is there you can go?

33:31.180 --> 33:34.660
The people are scared and they blame
you, and scared people

33:34.660 --> 33:35.980
do terrible things.

33:37.220 --> 33:38.980
They'll crucify you.

33:38.980 --> 33:40.540
They'll rip you to pieces!

33:40.540 --> 33:43.620
- People are animals.
- You don't think that.

33:43.620 --> 33:45.660
- Oh, I more than think it.

33:48.140 --> 33:50.180
- Are you a gambling man, Charlie?

33:55.380 --> 33:56.740
- Why?

33:58.420 --> 34:01.980
- Because I'm offering a wager.

34:01.980 --> 34:04.900
If you agree to let me go,

34:04.900 --> 34:07.180
we'll tell everyone where I am.

34:07.180 --> 34:11.300
Everyone - and then we'll see who
comes.

34:13.580 --> 34:16.100
- OK, looks like the priest's on
board.

34:16.100 --> 34:18.020
- What? He gave you a name?

34:18.020 --> 34:21.340
- Yeah, well, not in so many words,
but, yeah.

34:21.340 --> 34:24.500
I think I've talked him round. How'd
it go your end?

34:24.500 --> 34:26.900
Ready to spread the word?

34:26.900 --> 34:29.460
- I'm good to go.

34:29.460 --> 34:31.980
[KNOCKING]

34:40.980 --> 34:43.139
- It's me.

34:43.139 --> 34:44.900
Let me in.

34:44.900 --> 34:46.420
- No.

34:46.420 --> 34:49.300
- I will break down your door down
if I have to.

34:49.300 --> 34:50.699
- How-how did you find me?

34:50.699 --> 34:52.219
- ISP. You answered my e-mails.

34:53.620 --> 34:57.020
- Wait a minute! I thought that was
a booty call.

34:57.020 --> 34:58.300
You were playing me?

34:58.300 --> 35:00.660
- Like a Swanee whistle. Open the
door.

35:00.660 --> 35:04.020
- All that stuff about your son, was
that even true?

35:04.020 --> 35:05.780
- Of course not.

35:05.780 --> 35:09.260
- Oh, shit, Elaine! That... That's
pretty dark.

35:09.260 --> 35:11.300
That-that's not the sort of thing
you lie about!

35:11.300 --> 35:12.580
Your son tried to kill himself!

35:12.580 --> 35:14.420
- Well, you should've come to me
with this, Will -

35:14.420 --> 35:16.620
not just run to a newspaper, used it
to save yourself.

35:16.620 --> 35:18.900
- Oh! The reason I lost my job in
the first place is

35:18.900 --> 35:21.820
because you ran to a newspaper to do
exactly the same thing.

35:21.820 --> 35:23.900
- I've got something for you.

35:25.140 --> 35:26.700
Another story.

35:26.700 --> 35:29.460
- What story? Why?

35:29.460 --> 35:31.620
- Because I need it out there,
unofficially,

35:31.620 --> 35:34.340
and it cannot be traced to me, ever.

35:34.340 --> 35:36.340
- Why not?

35:36.340 --> 35:40.060
- Because I'm trying to catch a
spree killer before he kills anyone
else.

35:41.780 --> 35:43.860
And if I'm going to do that...

35:45.820 --> 35:47.580
...I need you...

35:50.500 --> 35:53.540
I need you to hang Dennis Chapman
out to dry for me.

36:17.860 --> 36:20.460
- All right, you need to understand
this, now.

36:20.460 --> 36:25.220
No-one is going to be protecting
you. No-one will be watching you.

36:25.220 --> 36:27.820
And no-one will help you. You are
completely alone.

36:30.860 --> 36:36.300
- One of the advantages of my line
of work - you're never alone.

36:53.860 --> 36:55.500
- Dennis.

36:55.500 --> 36:58.060
- Thank you for this.

36:59.740 --> 37:03.580
[RINGING]

37:04.980 --> 37:06.300
- Boss?

37:06.300 --> 37:07.700
- I need you to do me a favour.

37:07.700 --> 37:10.180
I need you to dig out an old file,
late '90s.

37:11.380 --> 37:13.260
Rape of a minor.

37:13.260 --> 37:15.620
- What, connected to this thing?

37:15.620 --> 37:17.100
- No. Listen...

37:17.100 --> 37:20.460
I wouldn't ask if it wasn't
important. You know that.

37:21.500 --> 37:23.780
- All right, give me the details.

37:27.740 --> 37:30.060
- Dennis, this sounds very risky.

37:30.060 --> 37:32.620
I'd like to stay with you, if I may?

37:36.460 --> 37:40.140
- I'd like it, too. But I can't have
that, Michael.

37:41.740 --> 37:45.140
I can't have your safety on my
conscience.

38:02.140 --> 38:05.500
- Not only has Father Dennis refused
all offers of protection,

38:05.500 --> 38:09.420
he's refused to put at risk anyone
whom the killer might believe

38:09.420 --> 38:13.940
to be helping him and thereby making
them a potential target.

38:13.940 --> 38:16.220
In the last few minutes, Father
Dennis

38:16.220 --> 38:18.580
has tweeted from an undisclosed
location,

38:18.580 --> 38:21.460
thanking people for their offers of
support.

38:21.460 --> 38:25.420
So all we know is, as London holds
its collective breath tonight,

38:25.420 --> 38:32.060
Father Dennis is alone, with his
God, his faith and his conscience.

38:32.060 --> 38:36.940
[RINGING]

38:36.940 --> 38:38.860
- He's done it. He's posted the
story.

38:38.860 --> 38:40.620
- OK, good.

38:40.620 --> 38:43.060
- And if the killer can smell what
we're doing?

38:43.060 --> 38:46.260
- Nah, he's too wrapped up in his
own shit to smell anything else.

38:46.260 --> 38:48.980
Look, he'll just think that it's
Dennis leaving him a message,

38:48.980 --> 38:52.420
you know - "Here I am. I'm alone and
I want to talk."

38:53.460 --> 38:55.740
Look, trust me, he's a gloating
bastard,

38:55.740 --> 38:57.460
he won't be able to resist it.

38:57.460 --> 38:59.740
- And how does Dennis feel about
that?

38:59.740 --> 39:02.020
- Well, he's pretending not to know
that's how it is.

39:02.020 --> 39:03.460
- What, that you've staked him out

39:03.460 --> 39:05.220
on a leash like the goat in Jurassic
Park?

39:05.220 --> 39:08.980
- Yeah, I believe it's called a lie
of omissions - you don't ask,

39:08.980 --> 39:10.540
you don't tell.

39:10.540 --> 39:13.060
Look, I need you here as soon as you
can.

39:14.060 --> 39:15.900
- All right, I'm on my way.

39:17.180 --> 39:18.300
- All right.

39:33.580 --> 39:35.580
- Any news on the flash drive?

39:39.700 --> 39:41.300
- No, not as such.

39:42.740 --> 39:45.420
Although, er, something you said did
ring a bell.

39:46.700 --> 39:48.660
Something about trusting your enemy.

39:50.340 --> 39:51.500
- Go on.

39:55.540 --> 40:00.700
- All right, look, when she was 14,
Elaine Renko's parents

40:00.700 --> 40:04.300
brought in a complaint of rape,
against a teacher.

40:05.540 --> 40:08.980
Yeah, a guy named... Noah Underhill.

40:11.100 --> 40:12.900
He taught English.

40:14.780 --> 40:17.100
And then Elaine denied everything,

40:17.100 --> 40:19.500
claimed she'd been assaulted by a
stranger,

40:19.500 --> 40:21.620
so the investigation didn't go
anywhere.

40:22.860 --> 40:26.140
- So she was a lying, intransigent
bitch even back then.

40:27.940 --> 40:29.860
Well, you do have to wonder why.

40:31.060 --> 40:33.300
- Well, not really.

40:33.300 --> 40:35.900
No, she was a kid. She was scared.

40:35.900 --> 40:38.460
You know, maybe she thought she was
in love.

40:38.460 --> 40:41.260
Maybe she just wanted it all to come
to an end.

40:41.260 --> 40:43.140
But whatever, she saved his career

40:43.140 --> 40:45.340
and most likely kept him out of
prison.

40:46.740 --> 40:49.860
So, if there's one favour she can
call on,

40:49.860 --> 40:52.500
one enemy she can trust...

40:55.220 --> 40:56.940
...well, he's your man.

40:58.700 --> 41:00.420
- This is good work, Charlie.

41:01.900 --> 41:04.220
This is really good.

41:04.220 --> 41:06.620
- Right, so now you need to make
good on your end.

41:08.620 --> 41:12.820
You make sure that my family are
well looked after.

41:14.980 --> 41:16.780
- Right up until the end.

41:19.060 --> 41:21.180
- And don't hurt her.

41:21.180 --> 41:24.020
Elaine. You don't need to hurt her.

41:44.980 --> 41:46.300
- Mishal.

41:46.300 --> 41:47.580
- Hm?

41:49.460 --> 41:51.020
- Miriam Blackwood.

41:51.020 --> 41:53.300
She was worried about her son -
devout Catholic,

41:53.300 --> 41:55.260
some kind of aid worker.

41:55.260 --> 41:58.620
Apparently, he worked with Dennis
Chapman at an inner-city
night-shelter.

41:58.620 --> 42:01.300
And here's his name, in Dennis'
address book.

42:02.620 --> 42:06.620
- OK. Let's check him out. I'll
update Counter Terror.

42:33.740 --> 42:35.700
- Armed police! Armed police!

42:38.340 --> 42:40.020
- Clear...
- Clear!

42:56.220 --> 42:59.220
- The Problem Of Pain.

42:59.220 --> 43:01.540
Evil And The Justice Of God.

43:02.820 --> 43:06.940
Reflections On Suffering And Evil.
On and on.

43:08.380 --> 43:10.340
- I'll get onto CT.

43:10.340 --> 43:12.580
- Looks like Blackwood's our man.

43:12.580 --> 43:14.780
- We've got a name for you.

43:57.940 --> 44:00.060
- Help me! Please! Somebody!

44:00.060 --> 44:01.700
- We should help.

44:01.700 --> 44:04.300
- The police warned us about helping
strangers.

44:04.300 --> 44:07.620
OK? It was on the news. Just call
999.

44:07.620 --> 44:10.060
- No, you call them.

44:10.060 --> 44:13.300
- Please! Somebody! Help me!
- Dia! Dia!

44:17.020 --> 44:18.700
Hey! What are you doing?

44:18.700 --> 44:20.140
- Ssh.

44:45.300 --> 44:46.540
Hello?

45:17.060 --> 45:18.780
Open the door, Andreas! Open up!

45:19.940 --> 45:22.420
Please help me!

45:22.420 --> 45:23.940
Oh, my God!

45:43.460 --> 45:44.700
[BUZZING]

45:46.340 --> 45:48.940
Yeah. What's up?

45:58.460 --> 45:59.780
They've got him.

45:59.780 --> 46:01.380
He's dead.

46:06.500 --> 46:07.900
So who is he?

46:07.900 --> 46:11.380
- William Cherry. 48. Unmarried
driving instructor.

46:11.380 --> 46:12.780
- Was he on the list?

46:12.780 --> 46:16.020
- Top of it. Counter Terrorism had
him flagged as prime suspect.

46:16.020 --> 46:18.900
History of psychiatric problems,
religious mania.

46:18.900 --> 46:21.180
Promising God's vengeance on
sinners.

46:21.180 --> 46:22.660
That sort of fun and games.

46:22.660 --> 46:24.900
- Yeah, but is there any connection
to Dennis Chapman?

46:24.900 --> 46:26.820
- Sorry, boss, not really.

46:26.820 --> 46:29.460
- Counter Terror's profiler thinks
it was random.

46:29.460 --> 46:31.900
They reckon he did make a
confession.

46:31.900 --> 46:33.220
You were right about that.

46:33.220 --> 46:36.860
He was probably in the first church
he stumbled across after killing
Jamie Unwin.

46:36.860 --> 46:38.780
- Oh, shit!

46:38.780 --> 46:41.460
All right, we'll leave the paperwork
to the victors.

46:41.460 --> 46:43.820
We'll tie this off tomorrow, yeah?

47:06.740 --> 47:10.100
[BANGING]

47:18.980 --> 47:21.260
I suppose I'd better tell Dennis
face-to-face.

47:21.260 --> 47:22.660
I at least owe him that.

47:22.660 --> 47:24.260
- Do you think he'll press charges?

47:24.260 --> 47:27.700
- Nah, the bloke's a Christian. Let
him forgive me.

47:27.700 --> 47:30.180
- So how do you say sorry for
waterboarding someone?

47:30.180 --> 47:33.860
- Yeah, all right, threatening to
waterboard someone - it's a
different kettle of fish.

47:33.860 --> 47:36.220
- Oh, completely.
- Why? Do you think I would have
done it?

47:36.220 --> 47:38.020
- You'd totally have done it.

47:45.780 --> 47:48.820
[BANGING]

48:23.980 --> 48:28.260
- Michael... I-I'm sorry, Michael.

48:28.260 --> 48:30.820
I-I don't understand.

48:30.820 --> 48:33.300
- Someone recognised the neon
crucifix.

48:35.020 --> 48:36.660
In your Tweet.

48:36.660 --> 48:38.780
When it was on the news.

48:38.780 --> 48:40.540
Word got around.

48:43.660 --> 48:46.860
I tried to intervene, but there was
no stopping them.

48:48.620 --> 48:50.300
They're here for you, Dennis.

48:51.580 --> 48:53.220
They're here to stand with you.

48:53.220 --> 48:54.820
And so am I.

48:58.380 --> 49:00.500
- Good evening, Father.

49:00.500 --> 49:01.860
- Good evening.

49:01.860 --> 49:04.420
[RINGING]

49:07.060 --> 49:09.020
George.

49:09.020 --> 49:11.700
- Boss, sorry to do this to you, but
they've got the wrong man.

49:11.700 --> 49:14.140
- What?
- The dead man at Thamesview was a
copycat.

49:14.140 --> 49:17.020
I think we're looking for a man
called Blackwood, Thomas Blackwood.

49:17.020 --> 49:19.580
- All right, on a scale of one to
ten, how sure are you?

49:19.580 --> 49:20.860
- Ten.

49:20.860 --> 49:22.980
Well, nine point something
recurring.

49:22.980 --> 49:24.740
But I'm in a minority of one.

49:24.740 --> 49:27.460
I already reported this to Counter
Terror and to Bell,

49:27.460 --> 49:29.940
but they don't want to hear it. But
they're wrong.

49:31.060 --> 49:33.460
- All right, now, listen, you send
me what you've got.

49:33.460 --> 49:36.220
You tell Armed Response to go to The
Sacred Heart Church

49:36.220 --> 49:38.500
and to do it quietly.

49:38.500 --> 49:40.380
- On our way.
- All right, good.

49:40.380 --> 49:42.620
Right, he's saying we've got the
wrong man on the slab.

49:42.620 --> 49:45.340
- Do you think he's in there?
- Oh, shit, I don't know.

49:45.340 --> 49:47.020
I've been trying to tickle him out.

49:47.020 --> 49:49.420
I didn't expect the Glastonbury
festival to turn up.

49:49.420 --> 49:52.220
- Well, we can't wait for Armed
Response.

49:55.260 --> 49:57.380
- It's very moving.

50:49.340 --> 50:51.220
Erm...

50:51.220 --> 50:54.860
I look at your faces...

50:56.500 --> 51:00.060
...and you all seem

51:00.060 --> 51:07.020
so content in your bravery and
goodness.

51:08.460 --> 51:11.780
So keen to be congratulated.

51:12.940 --> 51:19.020
But, looking out at the faces before
me...

51:20.820 --> 51:23.620
...I don't see goodness.

51:23.620 --> 51:29.540
And I don't see self-sacrifice.

51:29.540 --> 51:32.940
I see a rabble

51:32.940 --> 51:35.500
of complacent

51:35.500 --> 51:38.460
self-satisfied

51:38.460 --> 51:40.060
narcissists.

51:41.140 --> 51:47.620
Now, you... You may not like what
I'm saying,

51:47.620 --> 51:55.060
but it's truth, and the truth will
save you.

51:56.660 --> 51:58.300
You're contemptible.

51:59.380 --> 52:03.020
And I need you out of here.

52:03.020 --> 52:05.780
All of you, out of my sight!

52:07.780 --> 52:09.100
- No!

52:16.060 --> 52:19.020
- Leave! Everyone! Go!

52:23.100 --> 52:25.260
[SCREAMING]

52:35.180 --> 52:39.940
- Ha, ha, ha! Oh, yes, Dennis!

52:42.420 --> 52:47.580
You were telling the truth up there.
That's all I wanted.

52:47.580 --> 52:49.740
For you to know the truth.

52:49.740 --> 52:50.980
- Stop!

52:52.220 --> 52:53.580
Enough!

52:55.020 --> 52:57.020
Bring him here.

53:12.660 --> 53:19.420
He tried to attack me and I defended
myself as best I could,

53:19.420 --> 53:22.860
until you managed to restrain him.

53:22.860 --> 53:26.300
- Are you sure you want to do this
to yourself, Dennis?

53:26.300 --> 53:28.220
- It's already done.

53:55.580 --> 53:57.140
Can you hear Him now, Thom?

53:58.540 --> 53:59.980
Can you hear Him?

54:02.540 --> 54:04.100
Because I can.

54:05.540 --> 54:06.580
Oh, I can hear Him.

54:07.900 --> 54:10.100
Oh, yes!

54:10.100 --> 54:12.580
- Oh, oh, Dennis!

54:14.100 --> 54:15.420
- Do you hear that?

54:17.380 --> 54:20.180
Do you hear Him, Thom?

54:31.140 --> 54:34.660
- I DON'T HEAR ANYTHING!

56:54.540 --> 56:56.980
- Hi, I'm Gretchen Ross from Social
Services.

56:56.980 --> 56:59.860
- Someone on high wants Charlie
Hicks.

56:59.860 --> 57:01.900
- You just keep your people out of
my way.

57:01.900 --> 57:03.620
- Could you just look him in the eye

57:03.620 --> 57:05.820
and... tell him it wasn't his fault?

57:05.820 --> 57:08.860
- I will kill you stone dead.

57:08.860 --> 57:11.140
I will finish you!

57:11.140 --> 57:13.180
- I just want to treasure what we've
got...

57:13.180 --> 57:14.460
...while we've got it.

57:14.460 --> 57:16.500
- I can take it all away.

57:16.500 --> 57:18.860
All the people you love.

57:18.860 --> 57:20.460
- Here they come...

57:21.780 --> 57:23.420
...ready or not.

57:26.980 --> 57:28.620
- Oh...

57:28.620 --> 57:30.780
...here comes trouble.

